The article discusses President Obama's trip to El Paso, Texas, where he will deliver a speech on the importance of fixing the broken immigration system for economic and security needs. The President will also discuss fostering a constructive national conversation on immigration and building a bipartisan consensus in Congress. Prior to the speech, President Obama will tour the cargo facility at the Bridge of the Americas Port of Entry. The article also mentions the President's recent meetings with leaders from various sectors to discuss the need to fix the immigration system. It further highlights upcoming community conversations organized around the country to elevate the immigration debate.